  "texts": [
    "Also, MEDIC is effectively employed for disease Named Entity Recognition (NER) within PubTator Central 25 which provides advanced automatic annotation tools for biomedical concepts, including genes and diseases, within both PubMed abstracts and PubMed Central full-text articles.",
    "Furthermore, MEDIC has been widely adopted in various studies that involve the construction of corpora based on PubMed abstracts 22, 26.",
    "Additionally, every disease term in MEDIC is assigned a corresponding MeSH Unique ID.",
    "This makes MEDIC an ideal disease vocabulary for creating a TFDR corpus, as it enables seamless integration with articles indexed in PubMed, ensuring precise and comprehensive disease term mapping.",
    "Therefore, in this study, CTD's MEDIC was chosen as the disease vocabulary."
